               <head>Laṭāʼif al-ṭavāʻif by ʻAlī ibn Ḥusayn Vāʻiẓ Kāshifī Ṣafī</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>A collection of anecdotes by Fakhr al-Dīn ʿAlī ibn Ḥusayn Vāʿiẓ Kāshifī
                     known as al-Ṣafī (1463-1532 or 3), the son of Ḥusayn Vāʿiẓ Kāshifī, who
                     compiled it in Gharjistan for the amusement of the Sulṭān, S̲h̲āh Muḥammad. </summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002009961"
                     n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3780-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"
                           key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658925.0x000001 viaf_90077852">ʿAlī ibn Ḥusayn
                           Vāʿiẓ al-Kāshifī Ṣafī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_90077852">على بن حسين واعظ كاشفى
                           صفى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_5080">Laṭāʾif al-ṭavāʾif</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_5080">لطائف الطوائف</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
